-- CCU May Enter Third Latin American Beverage Market, Pulso Says
-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 2012-01-04T12:30:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-04/ccu-may-enter-third-latin-american-beverage-market-pulso-says.html
Cia. Cervecerias Unidas SA (CCU) , which
brews beer in Chile and  Argentina , is considering entry into a
third Latin American market, Chief Executive Officer Patricio Jottar told  Pulso .  Peru, Uruguay,  Paraguay  and  Colombia  are possibilities, the
Santiago-based newspaper quoted Jottar as saying. CCU, which
also distributes non-alcoholic beverages, is looking to expand
into dairy products and is open to alliances in the ready-to-eat
foods segment,  Pulso  reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
 ethomson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  